<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Date on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/date/</link><description>Recent content in Date on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/date/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Financial Toolbox: invalid date format in MATLAB</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-financial-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/matlab/matlab-financial-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Financial Toolbox errors occur when date formats are incorrect, financial data is invalid, or calculations encounter mathematical issues like division by zero.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid date string format&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Date conversion errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cash flow timing issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Zero or negative interest rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mismatched date vectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Invalid date format&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;d = datenum(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-13-01&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Error: month 13 invalid&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Valid date format&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;d = datenum(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-01-15&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% WRONG: Mismatched dates&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;StartDates = datenum({&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-01-01&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-02-01&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EndDates = datenum({&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-12-31&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;}); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Different count&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rates = [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.05&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.06&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;princ = yearfrac(StartDates, EndDates, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Match date vectors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;StartDates = datenum({&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-01-01&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-02-01&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EndDates = datenum({&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-12-31&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-12-31&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rates = [&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.05&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.06&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;princ = yearfrac(StartDates, EndDates, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% Works&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Validate dates&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; d = &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;safeDate&lt;/span&gt;(dateStr)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; d = datenum(dateStr);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Invalid date format: %s&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, dateStr);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-matlab" data-lang="matlab"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;% CORRECT: Financial calculations with validation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; pv = &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;presentValue&lt;/span&gt;(cashFlows, rates, dates)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; any(rates &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Interest rates must be non-negative&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; length(cashFlows) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;~=&lt;/span&gt; length(dates)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Cash flows and dates must have same length&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; pv = cfdates(cashFlows, dates);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-statistics-error"&gt;Statistics Error&lt;/a&gt; - data issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-table-error"&gt;Table Error&lt;/a&gt; - data format&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="matlab-string-error"&gt;String Error&lt;/a&gt; - conversion issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Java Date.getYear()/getMonth() Deprecated — Use LocalDate</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/java/date-methods/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/java/date-methods/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-java-dategetyeargetmonth-deprecated--use-localdate"&gt;[Solution] Java Date.getYear()/getMonth() Deprecated — Use LocalDate&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;java.util.Date&lt;/code&gt; class was deprecated shortly after its release in JDK 1.1 because it was poorly designed — it mixed date and time, was not thread-safe, and had confusing APIs like &lt;code&gt;getYear()&lt;/code&gt; returning years since 1900. The &lt;code&gt;java.time&lt;/code&gt; package introduced in Java 8 (JSR 310) is the modern replacement, with &lt;code&gt;LocalDate&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;LocalTime&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;LocalDateTime&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;ZonedDateTime&lt;/code&gt; as the primary classes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The compiler warning when using deprecated &lt;code&gt;Date&lt;/code&gt; methods:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PHP Warning: date() Timezone Database — Set date.timezone Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/warning-date/</link><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/warning-date/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="php-warning-date-timezone-database"&gt;PHP Warning: date(): Timezone Database&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This warning appears when PHP cannot determine the correct timezone for date and time functions. It typically occurs when &lt;code&gt;date.timezone&lt;/code&gt; is not set in &lt;code&gt;php.ini&lt;/code&gt; or when the system timezone cannot be inferred from the OS configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;date.timezone&lt;/code&gt; is missing or commented out in &lt;code&gt;php.ini&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The server&amp;rsquo;s OS timezone is not set or is set to an unrecognized value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;date()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;time()&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;strtotime()&lt;/code&gt; without an explicit timezone context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling date functions in a containerized environment with no timezone configured&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-set-datetimezone-in-phpini"&gt;1. Set &lt;code&gt;date.timezone&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;code&gt;php.ini&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The most straightforward fix — define the default timezone in your PHP configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>